text: Seguenzia antarctica is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Seguenziidae. ==Description== The height of the shell attains 5 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Weddell Sea, Antarctica. ==References== * Engl W. (2012) Shells of Antarctica. Hackenheim: Conchbooks. 402 pp. antarctica Category:Gastropods described in 1925
title: Seguenzia antarctica
